The paper deals with decision problems related to timed automata, which are a type of formal language model used in computer science. The paper discusses undecidability results for several problems, including determinizability, complementation, minimization, and shuffling of timed automata. These topics are closely related to the areas of logic (cs.LO), formal languages (cs.FL), programming languages (cs.PL), data structures (cs.DS), and computational complexity (cs.CC). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
